title: House Republicans fail to override Biden's 1st presidential veto
description: House Republicans failed to override Biden's veto of a resolution against ESG investing

title: Chicago residents sound alarm after 2 women found dead, teen missing
description: Two women were found dead in recent weeks, and a teenager is now missing in Chicago's Little Village neighborhood, community leaders said.

title: Judge temporarily blocks Wyoming abortion ban, allowing abortions to resume
description: A Wyoming judge temporarily blocked a state abortion ban that passed last week. The ban prohibits nearly all abortions with few exceptions.

title: Langston University clears over $4.5 million in student debt balances
description: Langston University, a historically black institution in Oklahoma, announced the clearance of over $4.5 million in student debt balances.

title: Alec Baldwin claims prosecutor in 'Rust' case violated his constitutional rights
description: Alec Baldwin's attorneys claimed that the now-former special prosecutor who investigated the fatal "Rust" shooting used the case to advance her career.

title: Rioter charged in Pelosi laptop theft sentenced to prison
description: A Pennsylvania woman linked to a far-right extremist movement has been sentenced to three years in prison for storming the U.S. Capitol and invading then-House Speaker Nancy Pelosi’s office with other rioters

title: NTSB: Crews failed to de-ice road before massive Texas crash
description: Federal officials say that the company responsible for maintaining a Texas interstate where 130 vehicles crashed in icy conditions two years ago, killing six, failed to address the deteriorating road conditions

title: LA schools strike enters 3rd day as bargaining resumes
description: More than 30,000 picketing Los Angeles school service employees are expected to return to work on Friday after a planned three-day strike and a return to bargaining.

title: Cost of India quitting coal is $900 billion, think tank says
description: India will require $900 billion over the next 30 years to move away from coal mines and thermal plants, a New Delhi based think tank said in a report Thursday

title: Fetterman expected back 'soon,' but no certain timeline yet
description: The office of Pennsylvania Sen. John Fetterman says he's expected to return to the chamber soon after seeking inpatient treatment for clinical depression

title: Feds: Woman charged in Wyoming clinic fire opposes abortion
description: Authorities say a woman accused of setting fire last year to a Wyoming abortion clinic that was under construction told investigators that she opposes abortion and was experiencing anxiety and nightmares over the facility opening

title: Pilot suffers medical emergency on flight, off-duty pilot helps land plane
description: An pilot from another airline helped to co-pilot a Southwest flight after one of its pilots suffered a medical emergency, officials said.

title: Hungary would not act on Putin arrest warrant, official says
description: The chief of staff to Hungary's prime minister says Hungarian authorities wouldn't arrest Russian President Vladimir Putin if he were to enter the country despite him being the subject of an international warrant for alleged war crimes in Ukraine

title: Average long-term US mortgage rate falls to 6.42% this week
description: The average long-term U.S. mortgage fell for the second straight week, which combined with moderating home prices, could give the housing market a boost as the spring buying season begins

title: Parents of Michigan high school shooter will go to trial, judges rule
description: The parents of Michigan school shooter Ethan Crumbley will stand trial.

title: Police: Crypto firm founder Do Kwon arrested in Montenegro
description: Police in Montenegro say they have arrested Terraform Labs founder Do Kwon, who is wanted in South Korea in connection with a $40 billion crash of the firm’s cryptocurrency

title: South Carolina comptroller to resign after $3.5B error
description: Embattled South Carolina Comptroller General Richard Eckstrom will resign next month after a $3.5 billion accounting error in the year-end financial report he oversaw

title: NC approves Medicaid expansion, reversing long opposition
description: The Republican-controlled North Carolina legislature has given final approval to a Medicaid expansion agreement

title: TikTok CEO testimony on Capitol Hill updates: App faces possible ban
description: Lawmakers press TikTok CEO Shou Zi Chew over data security, misinformation and other issues.

title: Anger at Macron mounts as French unions hold new protests
description: Large crowds in Paris and other French cities have taken to the streets in the first mass demonstrations since President Emmanuel Macron inflamed public anger by forcing a higher retirement age bill through parliament without a vote

title: Reporter for Russian paper sentenced to 3 years in Belarus
description: A court in Belarus has sentenced a reporter for the now-closed local edition of one of Russia’s most popular newspapers to three years in prison for insulting the country’s authoritarian leader

title: Ford says EV unit losing billions, should be seen as startup
description: Ford’s electric vehicle business has lost $3 billion before taxes during the past two years and will lose a similar amount this year as the company invests heavily in the new technology

title: Death toll from Pakistan, Afghanistan quake rises to 21
description: Officials say the death toll from a magnitude 6.5 earthquake that struck much of Pakistan and neighboring Afghanistan earlier this week has risen to 21, after eight more deaths were reported in remote areas

title: Library association reports record book ban attempts in 2022
description: A new report from the American Library Association says attempted book bannings and restrictions at school and public libraries continue to surge, setting a record in 2022

title: US jobless claims inch down as labor market remains tight
description: The labor market continues to defy the Federal Reserve’s attempts at loosening it, with U.S. applications for unemployment benefits down again last week and remaining at historically low levels

title: WATCH:  Softball player scores in trick play
description: Carthage, Texas, high school senior Jada Walton used some creative thinking to distract the catcher as she tagged home plate.

title: 'Cancer Alley' at center of lawsuit claiming environmental health crisis
description: Residents of a Louisiana community known as “Cancer Alley” filed a lawsuit Tuesday alleging the area's petrochemical plants are tantamount to “environmental racism.”

title: Hyundai, Kia recall vehicles due to fire risk
description: Hyundai and Kia are telling owners of over 571,000 SUVs and minivans in the U.S. to park them outdoors because the tow hitch harnesses can catch fire while they are parked or being driven

title: Slim pickings for buyers amid near-record low homes for sale
description: Americans eager to buy a home this spring, beware: It’s slim pickings out there

title: Credit Suisse deal halted crisis, Swiss national bank says
description: The Swiss central bank has hiked its key interest rate and insisted that a government-orchestrated takeover of troubled Credit Suisse by rival bank UBS ended the financial turmoil

title: Launch debut of 3D-printed rocket ends in failure, no orbit
description: A rocket made almost entirely of 3D-printed parts has finally taken flight, but didn't last long

title: UK central bank may hike rates after big jump in food prices
description: A shortage of fresh vegetables last month may force the Bank of England to approve an 11th consecutive interest rate increase Thursday

title: US denies Chinese claim it drove away American destroyer
description: The U.S. is denying Chinese claims that its military had driven away an American guided-missile destroyer from operating around disputed islands in the South China Sea, in an incident that comes as tensions in the region between the two powers continue...

title: EU leaders set to endorse more military support for Ukraine
description: EU leaders are set to endorse a deal aimed at sending Ukraine 1 million rounds of artillery shells within the next 12 months to help the country repel Russia’s invasion forces

title: California lawmakers to vote on possible gas price penalties
description: California lawmakers are preparing to vote on whether to allow penalties on oil companies for price gouging

title: Lindsay Lohan, other celebs settle with SEC over crypto case
description: Actress Lindsay Lohan, rapper Akon and several other celebrities have agreed to pay tens of thousands of dollars to settle claims they promoted crypto investments to their millions of social media followers without disclosing they were being paid to do so

title: Shelter-in-place issued at Monmouth University due to possible armed suspect
description: Monmouth University in West Long Branch, New Jersey, has issued a shelter-in-place order due to a "possible armed subject."

title: COVID-19 death rates varied dramatically across US, major analysis finds
description: A new analysis published Monday found COVID-19 deaths varied dramatically across the U.S. with Arizona having the highest rates and Hawaii having the lowest.
